definition.value: A primary alcohol that is uracil bearing a hydroxymethyl substituent at the 5-position.
A member of the class of dihydroflavonols that is the 2,3-dihydro derivative of gossypetin.
A polysaccharide composed of two or more different types of monosaccharides,
An oxo dicarboxylate obtained by removal of a proton from both of the carboxylic acid groups of (Z)-5-oxohex-2-enedioic acid.
